  "content": "\u003cp\u003eAm I crazy or does the UX of mastodon kind of suck in some places?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;ve seen \u0026quot;Share on Mastodon\u0026quot; buttons on websites and are greeted with a prompt saying \u0026quot;what\u0026#39;s your mastodon instance so you can actually post\u0026quot;. I get that mastodon is federated... but there has to be a better UX for this. It\u0026#39;s things that this that absolutely turn off normies who just want to share stuff to their friends.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI have absolutely no proposal for how to improve this. I\u0026#39;m just complaining\u003c/p\u003e",
